or has accepted an order for 500 chairs, 100 benches, and 150 tables, which must be supplied to avoid a financial penalty of $2,000.\"", "\"SPECIALIST TIMBER\":\"Specialist timber is a type of timber that is limited in supply to 20,000 square meters per annum due to a problem with the supplier.\"", "\"LINEAR PROGRAMMING FOR OPTIMAL PRODUCTION PLAN WITH RESOURCE CONSTRAINTS\":\"A company uses linear programming to establish an optimal production plan to maximize profit, considering constraints on materials and labor. The company must meet a minimum order requirement for one of its products while optimizing the use of limited resources.\"", "\"CONSTRAINT EQUATIONS\":\"Constraint equations in linear programming are mathematical expressions that represent the limitations or requirements of the problem. In this case, the constraints include the availability of materials and labor, as well as the minimum order requirement for product A.\"", "\"GRAPHICAL SOLUTION\":\"Graphical solution involves plotting the constraints on a 2D line chart to determine the optimal production plan. The optimal point is the intersection of the lines: a = 1,000 and materials constraint 3a + 4b = 30,000.\"", "\"OPTIMAL PRODUCTION PLAN\":\"The optimal production plan is to make 1,000 units of A and 6,750 units of B.\"", "\"OPTIMAL PRODUCTION STRATEGY FOR TABLET CO USING LINEAR PROGRAMMING\":\"Tablet Co makes two types of tablet computers, the Xeno (X) and the Yong (Y). The company uses linear programming to determine the optimal production plan to maximize contribution, considering constraints in build, program, and test stages.\"", "\"CONTRIBUTION FUNCTION\":\"Contribution function: C = 30x + 40y, where x is the number of units of Xeno to be produced and y is the number of units of Yong to be produced.\"", "\"DRILLING PROGRAMME\":\"A drilling programme refers to the planned activities and operations involved in drilling for oil. The success of this programme is dependent on prior geological testing and the likelihood of finding commercially viable quantities of oil.\"", "\"NET PRESENT VALUE (NPV)\":\"Net present value (NPV) is a financial metric that calculates the present value of all cash inflows and outflows associated with a project, discounted at a specific rate. It is used to assess the profitability of an investment.\"", "\"DECISION TREE\":\"A decision tree is a graphical representation of possible solutions to a decision based on certain conditions. It helps in identifying the best course of action by mapping out different decision paths and their potential outcomes.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}